    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tree that grows in parts of Africa, Central and South America, the West Indies, and extreme southern Florida. It is used as an ornamental, for traditional systems of medicine, and for its fruits that are used as vessels.</Note_Text>
